<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="324" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="19.[807,1395,1470,1892]" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">
<emphasis box="[807,962,1470,1499]" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas &amp; Wroughton, 1907" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Wroughton" authorityYear="1907" class="Mammalia" family="Herpestidae" genus="Crossarchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="19" pageNumber="324" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alexandri">Crossarchus alexandri Thomas &amp; Wroughton, 1907</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3699972309" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">
Ubangi, 
<collectingCountry name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
(formerly 
<collectingCountry box="[1282,1360,1549,1578]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">Zaire</collectingCountry>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[807,1395,1470,1892]" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">
Two subspecies were recognized by Goldman in 1984, who proposed minor as restricted to eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1230,1662,1695]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry name="Uganda" pageId="19" pageNumber="324">Uganda</collectingCountry>
. However, subsequent research has discounted the subspecies status of this population and returned this species to monotypic status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
